Chapter 1 Exploration of progenitors as defined in Delile et al.

1.1 Fetch MouseSpinalCordAtlas data

1.2 Load pre-filtered data

# Load pre-filtered data
data_seurat <- readRDS(file = paste0(path_rds, "seurat_cell_select.rds"))

# Load Table S1 from original paper
table_s1 <- read.csv2(file = paste0(path_raw, "TableS1.csv"),
                      header = TRUE)
rownames(table_s1) <- table_s1[,'Gene']
table_s1 <- table_s1[, -1]
DT::datatable(table_s1)
# Load annotated data from original paper
phenoData_annotated <- read.delim2(paste0(path_raw, "phenoData_annotated.csv"),
                                   header = TRUE,
                                   sep = '\t')
rownames(phenoData_annotated) <- phenoData_annotated[,'X']
phenoData_annotated <- phenoData_annotated[, -1]
dim(phenoData_annotated)
## [1] 41025     8
DT::datatable(phenoData_annotated)
Idents(data_seurat) <- 'timepoint'
table(Idents(data_seurat))
## 
##  9.5 10.5 11.5 12.5 13.5 
## 1938 3508 5000 6877 8251
DimPlot(object = data_seurat, reduction = 'umap')

phenoData_annotated_filt <- phenoData_annotated[rownames(data_seurat@meta.data),]
dim(phenoData_annotated_filt)
## [1] 25574     8
head(phenoData_annotated_filt)

1.3 Visualize Progenitors and Neurons

Idents(data_seurat) <- 'Type_step1'
data_sub <- data_seurat[, which(data_seurat@meta.data$Type_step1 == 'Progenitor' |
                                data_seurat@meta.data$Type_step1 == 'Neuron' |
                                data_seurat@meta.data$Type_step1 == 'Outliers' |
                                data_seurat@meta.data$Type_step1 == 'NULL')]
DimPlot(object = data_sub)
